  "root_text": {
    "an5.40:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5.40 ",
    "an5.40:0.2": "4. Sumanavagga ",
    "an5.40:0.3": "Mahāsālaputtasutta ",
    "an5.40:1.1": "“Himavantaṁ, bhikkhave, pabbatarājaṁ nissāya mahāsālā pañcahi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an5.40:1.2": "Katamāhi pañcahi? ",
    "an5.40:1.3": "Sākhāpattapalāsena vaḍḍhanti; ",
    "an5.40:1.4": "tacena vaḍḍhanti; ",
    "an5.40:1.5": "papaṭikāya vaḍḍhanti; ",
    "an5.40:1.6": "pheggunā vaḍḍhanti; ",
    "an5.40:1.7": "sārena vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an5.40:1.8": "Himavantaṁ, bhikkhave, pabbatarājaṁ nissāya mahāsālā imāhi pañcahi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an5.40:1.9": "Evamevaṁ kho, bhikkhave, saddhaṁ kulaputtaṁ nissāya antojano pañcahi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhati. ",
    "an5.40:1.10": "Katamāhi pañcahi? ",
    "an5.40:1.11": "Saddhāya vaḍḍhati; ",
    "an5.40:1.12": "sīlena vaḍḍhati; ",
    "an5.40:1.13": "sutena vaḍḍhati; ",
    "an5.40:1.14": "cāgena vaḍḍhati; ",
    "an5.40:1.15": "paññāya vaḍḍhati. ",
    "an5.40:1.16": "Saddhaṁ, bhikkhave, kulaputtaṁ nissāya antojano imāhi pañcahi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhatīti. ",
    "an5.40:2.1": "Yathā hi pabbato selo, ",
    "an5.40:2.2": "araññasmiṁ brahāvane; ",
    "an5.40:2.3": "Taṁ rukkhā upanissāya, ",
    "an5.40:2.4": "vaḍḍhante te vanappatī. ",
    "an5.40:3.1": "Tatheva sīlasampannaṁ, ",
    "an5.40:3.2": "Saddhaṁ kulaputtaṁ imaṁ; ",
    "an5.40:3.3": "Upanissāya vaḍḍhanti, ",
    "an5.40:3.4": "Puttadārā ca bandhavā; ",
    "an5.40:3.5": "Amaccā ñātisaṅghā ca, ",
    "an5.40:3.6": "Ye cassa anujīvino. ",
    "an5.40:4.1": "Tyassa sīlavato sīlaṁ, ",
    "an5.40:4.2": "cāgaṁ sucaritāni ca; ",
    "an5.40:4.3": "Passamānānukubbanti, ",
    "an5.40:4.4": "ye bhavanti vicakkhaṇā. ",
    "an5.40:5.1": "Idha dhammaṁ caritvāna, ",
    "an5.40:5.2": "maggaṁ sugatigāminaṁ; ",
    "an5.40:5.3": "Nandino devalokasmiṁ, ",
    "an5.40:5.4": "modanti kāmakāmino”ti. ",
    "an5.40:5.5": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "an5.40:5.6": "Sumanavaggo catuttho. ",
    "an5.40:6.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "an5.40:6.1": "Sumanā cundī uggaho, ",
    "an5.40:6.2": "sīho dānānisaṁsako; ",
    "an5.40:6.3": "Kālabhojanasaddhā ca, ",
    "an5.40:6.4": "puttasālehi te dasāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an5.40:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 5.40 ",
    "an5.40:0.2": "4. With Sumanā ",
    "an5.40:0.3": "Great Sal Trees ",
    "an5.40:1.1": "“Mendicants, great sal trees grow in five ways supported by the Himalayas, the king of mountains. ",
    "an5.40:1.2": "What five? ",
    "an5.40:1.3": "The branches, leaves, and foliage; ",
    "an5.40:1.4": "the bark; ",
    "an5.40:1.5": "the shoots; ",
    "an5.40:1.6": "the softwood; ",
    "an5.40:1.7": "and the hardwood. ",
    "an5.40:1.8": "Great sal trees grow in these five ways supported by the Himalayas, the king of mountains. ",
    "an5.40:1.9": "In the same way, a family grows in five ways supported by a family head with faith. ",
    "an5.40:1.10": "What five? ",
    "an5.40:1.11": "Faith, ",
    "an5.40:1.12": "ethics, ",
    "an5.40:1.13": "learning, ",
    "an5.40:1.14": "generosity, ",
    "an5.40:1.15": "and wisdom. ",
    "an5.40:1.16": "A family grows in these five ways supported by a family head with faith. ",
    "an5.40:2.1": "Supported by the mountain crags ",
    "an5.40:2.2": "in the wilds, the formidable forest, ",
    "an5.40:2.3": "the tree grows ",
    "an5.40:2.4": "to become lord of the forest. ",
    "an5.40:3.1": "So too, when the family head ",
    "an5.40:3.2": "is ethical and faithful, ",
    "an5.40:3.3": "supported by them, they grow: ",
    "an5.40:3.4": "children, partners, and kin, ",
    "an5.40:3.5": "colleagues, relatives, ",
    "an5.40:3.6": "and those dependent for their livelihood. ",
    "an5.40:4.1": "Seeing the ethical conduct of the virtuous, ",
    "an5.40:4.2": "the generosity and good deeds, ",
    "an5.40:4.3": "those who see clearly ",
    "an5.40:4.4": "do likewise. ",
    "an5.40:5.1": "Having practiced the teaching here, ",
    "an5.40:5.2": "the path that goes to a good place, ",
    "an5.40:5.3": "they delight in the heavenly realm, ",
    "an5.40:5.4": "enjoying all the pleasures they desire.” ",
